{"lemma":"واحِد","slug":"واحِد","root":"#.ح.د","root_slug":"_-ح-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ح-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"واحِد","root":"وحد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":30},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","num","pron"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41742"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"one","examples":[{"text":"رَأَيْتُ رَجُلًا وَاحِدًا وَٱمْرَأَةً وَاحِدَةً","english":"I saw [only] one man and one woman."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"single"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unique, incomparable"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"a certain"},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"someone","examples":[{"text":"اَلزَّانِيَةُ وَٱلزَّانِي فَٱجْلِدُوا كُلَّ وَاحِدٍ مِنْهُمَا مِئَةَ جَلْدَةٍ","english":"As for female and male fornicators, give each one of them one hundred lashes"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Semitic *ʔaḥad- ~ *waḥad-\nArabic واحد\nInherited from Proto-Semitic *ʔaḥad- ~ *waḥad- (“one”)."},"ipa":["/waː.ħid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41742","headword_ar":"وَاحِدٌ","root":"wHd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first of the numbers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K:) syn. [in many cases, which will be shown below,] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadN","text_ar":"اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one alone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single"},{"kind":"text","text":"person or thing:] fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidapN","text_ar":"وَاحِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, Msb:) it sometimes receives the dual form; (L, K;) as in the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilotaqayonaA waAHidayoni","text_ar":"اـِلْتَقَيْنَا وَاحِدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We met, we being each of us one alone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; cited from a poet by IAar: or the dual form pertains to it in another sense, explained below, namely “ alone: ” (L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHiduwna","text_ar":"وَاحِدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHodaAnN","text_ar":"وُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHodaAnN","text_ar":"اُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L;) in the last of which,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the dammeh: (L:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anotumo HaY~N waAHidN","text_ar":"اَنْتُمْ حَىٌّ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N waAHiduwna","text_ar":"حَىٌّ وَاحِدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ye are one tribe, L) like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iro*imapN qaliyluwna","text_ar":"شِرْذِمَةٌ قَلِيلُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr, S, L:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=HaAdN","text_ar":"ا=حَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may also be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and therefore originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoHaAdN","text_ar":"اَوْحَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohaAdN","text_ar":"اَشْهَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhidN","text_ar":"شَاهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Th, Msb.) Its proper signification is A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no subdivision:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is secondarily applied to any existing thing; so that there is no number to which it may not be applied as an epithet; wherefore one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN waAHidapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ وَاحِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miAy^apN waAHidapN","text_ar":"مِايَةٌ وَاحِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One hundred"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib.) It is interchangeable for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadN","text_ar":"اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when used as an epithet applied to God; and in certain nouns of number. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^Hd","text_ar":"احد"},{"kind":"text","text":".] In most cases differing from these two, there is a difference in usage. The latter is used in affirmative phrases as a prefixed noun only, governing the noun which follows it in the gen. case; and is used absolutely in negative phrases: whereas the former is used in affirmative phrases as a prefixed n. and otherwise. (Msb.) [See, again, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHd","text_ar":"اَحد"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasotu fiY h`*aA AlA^amori bA^awoiHada","text_ar":"لَسْتُ فِى هٰذَا الاَمْرِ باَوِْحَدَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am not alone, without a parallel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watch, in this affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L, K: *) or simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am not alone in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L.) The fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHodaA='u","text_ar":"وَحْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not used. (S, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHodaAnN","text_ar":"اُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwHd","text_ar":"اوحد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is applied by a poet to dogs"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no equals"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"matches."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA waAHida lahu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا وَاحِدَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has no equal, like, parallel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"match."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, L.) ―         -b5-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One that has no equal; one unequalled."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN waAHidu dahorihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ وَاحِدُ دَهْرِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a person is the unequalled one of his age."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And in like manner, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholi zamaAnihi","text_ar":"اَهْلِ زَمَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^awoHadu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَوْحَدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a person is the unequalled one of the people of his time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) The pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwHd","text_ar":"اوحد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as well as of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAHd","text_ar":"واحد"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same sense] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHodaAnN","text_ar":"اُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHodaAnN","text_ar":"وُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwdaAnN","text_ar":"سُودَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidu A^um~ihi","text_ar":"وَاحِدُ اُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An unequalled son of his mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is an indeterminate expression, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiyju waHodihi","text_ar":"نَسِيجُ وَحْدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (Hishám, Fr. L.) ―         -b8-  Also, A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pre-eminent in knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in valour in war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K [in the CK, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baA^os","text_ar":"بَاْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAs","text_ar":"ناس"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in other qualities;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though having no equal, and thus being alone: (L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHodaAnN","text_ar":"وُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uHodAnN","text_ar":"اُحْدانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAHidu","text_ar":"الوَاحِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHadu","text_ar":"الاَحَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^awoHadu","text_ar":"الاَوْحَدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmutawaH~idu","text_ar":"المُتَوَحِّدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, K,) epithets applied to God,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The One, the Sole; He whose attribute is unity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) or the first signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the One in essence, who has no like nor equal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the second,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the One in attributes, beside whom there is no other:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the first,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the One who is not susceptible of division into parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions, nor of duplication, and who has no equal nor like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TL:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the One who has ever been alone, without companion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, L:) and there is no being but God to whom the first and second of these epithets are applicable together, or to whom the second is applicable alone. (T, L.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadN","text_ar":"اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^Hd","text_ar":"احد"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_inosaAnu waAlfarasu waAHidN fiY Aljinosi","text_ar":"الاـِنْسَانُ وَالفَرَسُ وَاحِدٌ فِى الجِنْسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The human being and the horse are one in genus."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayod waEamrowN waAHidN fiY Aln~awoEi","text_ar":"زَيْد وَعَمرْوٌ وَاحِدٌ فِى النَّوْعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd and 'Amr are one in species."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Singular, as opposed to plural:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuHodaAnN","text_ar":"وُحْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (The lexicons, passim.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbiY waA^aSoHaAbuka waAHidN","text_ar":"اَصْحَابِى وَاَصْحَابُكَ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy companions and my companions are one and the same"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljuluwsu waAlquEuwd waAHidN","text_ar":"الجُلُوسُ وَالقُعُود وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljlws","text_ar":"الجلوس"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqEwd","text_ar":"القعود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are one and the same"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) ―         -b13-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHiydN","text_ar":"وَحِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiYa Ea$ara","text_ar":"حَادِىَ عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", masc., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiyapa Ea$orapa","text_ar":"حَادِيَةَ عَشْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", fem.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eleventh."},{"kind":"text","text":"In this case, [and in similar instances, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiY waEi$oruwna","text_ar":"حَادِى وَعِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twentyfirst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAdY","text_ar":"حادى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAdyp","text_ar":"حادية"},{"kind":"text","text":"are formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidapN","text_ar":"وَاحِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by putting the first radical letter after the second. [When without the article, it is indecl.: but when rendered determinate by the article, the first word is decl.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HaAdiYa Ea$arahumo","text_ar":"هُوَ حَادِىَ عَشَرَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the eleventh of them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawomu AlHaAdiY Ea$ara","text_ar":"اليَوْمُ الحَادِى عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eleventh day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayolapu AlHaAdiyapu Ea$orapa","text_ar":"اللَّيْلَةُ الحَادِيَةُ عَشْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The eleventh night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISd, L.) [The rules respecting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiYa Ea$ara","text_ar":"حَادِىَ عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its fem. are the same as those respecting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaAliva Ea$ara","text_ar":"ثَالِثَ عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its fem., explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.] ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwaAHidapK","text_ar":"بِوَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaTo","text_ar":"فَقَطْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and is often used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albat~apa","text_ar":"البَتَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ur~uwHN","text_ar":"ذُرُّوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K","Fr","TA","T","M","TL","IAth"]}]}}